 /**
 * WISING TAX ENGINE — LAYER 1: INDIA SPECIALIST
 * Version 5.1 | April 2026
 *
 * PURPOSE
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * Collects all India-specific tax data after Layer 0 routes the user to
 * `india_only` or `dual`. This module is the single source of truth for
 * Indian residency classification, GTI assembly, and ITR data inputs.
 *
 * SCOPE CONTAINMENT
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * This file contains INDIA TAX LAW ONLY. All US-side concerns (PFIC, FBAR,
 * Form 8938, GILTI/NCTI, §1014 step-up basis, treaty tie-breaker cascade,
 * Closer Connection, W-Forms, FATCA, §962 election) are out of scope and
 * live in the future layer1_us module.
 *
 * THE RESIDENCY LOCK
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * The very first thing this module does is run the RS-001 logic and write
 * `residency_detail.final_india_residency_status`. This DERIVED field is
 * the LOCK that gates every subsequent section (DTAA, LRS, deductions
 * eligibility, scope of income). No section downstream of the lock may
 * be filled until the lock is set.
 *
 * v5.1 CHANGE LOG
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * 1. BUG FIX: `presumptive_scheme` converted from single enum to array of
 *    enum. DOM_Tax_03 §4.2 explicitly permits simultaneous election of
 *    s.44AE (transport) + s.44AD (other business) for the same taxpayer.
 *    Single-enum forced misrepresentation. Empty array = "none" (regular
 *    computation path).
 *
 * 2. BUG FIX: `nature_of_business` converted from single enum to array of
 *    enum. Real users routinely hold multiple classifications simultaneously
 *    (professional consulting + F&O + intraday). Single-enum broke the
 *    Reactive Re-evaluation architecture when new income streams were added
 *    mid-session.
 *
 * 3. NORMALIZED `goods_vehicles[]` template. Sub-fields `vehicle_type`,
 *    `gvw_tonnes`, `months_owned` are now formally declared as template
 *    object members, consistent with `asset_blocks[]` and `msme_payables[]`.
 *    Previously documented only as inline comments — not machine-parseable.
 *
 * 4. ADDED NR-scope gate to presumptive_scheme (commented). s.44AD and
 *    s.44ADA require resident assessee (lock IN ["ROR","RNOR"]); s.44AE has
 *    no residency restriction. Engine rejects NR users electing s.44AD or
 *    s.44ADA with NR_INELIGIBLE_PRESUMPTIVE flag.
 *
 * 5. NEW FIELDS (20 additions, +8 CONDITIONAL +12 OPTIONAL):
 *
 *    Opening / Closing Stock (DOM_Tax_03 §11.3) — inventory businesses
 *      - `opening_stock_inr`, `closing_stock_inr` (CONDITIONAL)
 *
 *    TDS Default Disallowances (DOM_Tax_03 §9.2)
 *      - `expenses.payments_to_non_residents_no_tds_inr` — s.40(a)(i),
 *        100% disallowed
 *      - `expenses.payments_to_residents_no_tds_inr` — s.40(a)(ia),
 *        30% disallowed
 *
 *    Scientific Research (DOM_Tax_03 §7.5) — post-FA-2023 flat 100%
 *      - `expenses.s35_own_revenue_research_inr` (s.35(1)(i))
 *      - `expenses.s35_own_capital_research_inr` (s.35(2))
 *      - `expenses.s35_donation_to_approved_body_inr` (s.35(1)(ii)/(2AA))
 *
 *    Preliminary Expenses Amortisation (DOM_Tax_03 §7.6)
 *      - `expenses.s35D_total_preliminary_expenses_inr` — 1/5th over 5 AYs
 *      - `expenses.s35D_year_of_commencement` (CONDITIONAL)
 *
 *    VRS Amortisation (DOM_Tax_03 §7.7)
 *      - `expenses.s35DDA_vrs_payments_inr` — 1/5th over 5 AYs
 *      - `expenses.s35DDA_first_year_of_payment` (CONDITIONAL)
 *
 *    STT / CTT Audit Trail (DOM_Tax_03 §6.3) — NOT deductible, recorded
 *    for reconciliation
 *      - `expenses.stt_paid_inr`, `expenses.ctt_paid_inr`
 *
 *    Deemed Business Income (DOM_Tax_03 §11.1)
 *      - `s41_remission_income_inr` — s.41(1) liability cessation
 *      - `s41_bad_debt_recovery_inr` — s.41(4) recovery of prior write-off
 *
 *    AMT Credit Brought Forward (DOM_Tax_03 §13, s.115JC)
 *      - `amt_credit_bf_inr` — 15-year carry forward
 *      - `amt_credit_bf_origin_ay` (CONDITIONAL) — drives expiry computation
 *
 * 6. NO CHANGES to any other section (profile, residency_detail, dtaa,
 *    compliance_docs, bank_accounts, nro_repatriation, property,
 *    financial_holdings, commodities, unlisted_equity, share_buyback,
 *    other_sources, deductions, carry_forward_losses, lrs_outbound,
 *    tax_credits, surcharge_buckets, metadata except schema_version tag).
 *
 * v5.0 CHANGE LOG
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * 1. EXPANDED `business_income` block to support DOM_Tax_03 v2.0:
 *    - ADDED `nature_of_business`, `profession_type` for classification.
 *    - ADDED `digital_receipts_inr`, `cash_receipts_inr` for s.44AD
 *      blended rate computation (6% digital / 8% cash).
 *    - ADDED `s44AD_last_exit_ay`, `s44AD_opted_current_year` for
 *      5-year re-entry ban enforcement under s.44AD(4).
 *    - ADDED `goods_vehicles` array for s.44AE per-vehicle computation.
 *    - ADDED `gst_registration_status`, `gst_collected_inr` for correct
 *      taxable turnover derivation (GST collected is liability, not income).
 *    - REPLACED single `expenses_inr` with structured `expenses` sub-block
 *      covering s.30–s.37 categories, s.40A(3) cash disallowance,
 *      s.40A(2) related party flagging, and s.43B actual payment rule.
 *    - REPLACED single `depreciation_inr` with `asset_blocks` array for
 *      WDV block-wise computation, half-year rule, additional depreciation
 *      s.32(1)(iia), and s.32AD backward area allowance.
 *    - ADDED `speculative_turnover_inr` for intraday s.44AB audit gate
 *      (sum of abs(individual trade P&L), not net position).
 *    - ADDED `partner_income` sub-block for firm/LLP partner taxation,
 *      distinguishing entity_type for s.40(b) deductibility limits.
 *    - ADDED `msme_payables` array for s.43B(h) (Finance Act 2023)
 *      disallowance of overdue payments to micro/small enterprises.
 *
 * 2. NO CHANGES to any other section (profile, residency_detail, dtaa,
 *    compliance_docs, bank_accounts, nro_repatriation, property,
 *    financial_holdings, commodities, unlisted_equity, share_buyback,
 *    other_sources, deductions, carry_forward_losses, lrs_outbound,
 *    tax_credits, surcharge_buckets, metadata).
 *
 * v4.0 CHANGE LOG
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * 1. REMOVED `india_source_income_exact_inr` — replaced with boolean
 *    `india_source_income_above_15l`. The exact income amount is not
 *    needed to set the residency lock; a boolean unblocks the lock
 *    without forcing premature income math.
 *
 * 2. ADDED `came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen` — new boolean that
 *    distinguishes the 120-day Condition C visitor path from the
 *    standard 60-day path. Enabled only when employment_or_crew_status
 *    = "none" (visitors, not departing employees).
 *
 * 3. ADDED DERIVED `liable_to_tax_in_another_country_being_indian_citizen`
 *    — composite boolean that combines two Layer 0 pre-fills. TRUE only
 *    when is_indian_citizen = true AND liable_to_tax_in_another_country
 *    = true. This is the Deemed Resident blocker per s.6(1A).
 *
 * 4. ALL ENABLED IF gates updated to match the exhaustive boolean logic
 *    matrix from the India Residency (Tax Engine Logic) document.
 *
 * 5. Lock derivation cascade completely rewritten with the exhaustive
 *    ROR (2 paths), RNOR (9 paths), NR (8 paths) matrix.
 *
 * 6. `employment_or_crew_status` gate tightened: now requires
 *    days >= 60 AND < 182 AND preceding_4yr >= 365 AND indian_citizen,
 *    not just Layer 0 left_india_for_employment = true.
 *
 * 7. `nr_years_last_10_gte_9` and `days_in_india_last_7_years_lte_729`
 *    gates updated: now enabled if days >= 182 OR
 *    came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen = false (per document).
 *
 * UNLOCK LOGIC (enforced by frontend + backend)
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * Active when: tax_years.jurisdiction IN ("india_only", "dual")
 *
 *   Screen 2A → profile + residency_detail   (always shown; sets the LOCK)
 *   Screen 2B → dtaa                         (ENABLED IF lock = "NR")
 *   Screen 2C → compliance_docs              (ENABLED IF dtaa.tax_residency_country is set)
 *   Screen 2D → bank_accounts                (ENABLED IF lock IN ["NR","RNOR","ROR"])
 *   Screen 2E → property                     (ENABLED IF property.has_indian_property_transaction = true)
 *   Screen 2F → financial_holdings           (always shown)
 *   Screen 2G → commodities                  (always shown, gated by has_commodity_transactions)
 *   Screen 2H → unlisted_equity              (always shown, gated)
 *   Screen 2I → share_buyback                (always shown, gated)
 *   Screen 2J → domestic_income              (always shown)
 *   Screen 2K → other_sources                (always shown, sub-fields gated)
 *   Screen 2L → deductions                   (ENABLED IF profile.tax_regime = "OLD"
 *                                              OR lock IN ["RNOR","ROR"] for auto-comparison)
 *   Screen 2M → carry_forward_losses         (always shown, gated)
 *   Screen 2N → lrs_outbound                 (ENABLED IF lock = "ROR")
 *   Screen 2O → tax_credits                  (always shown, progressive)
 *
 * CONVENTIONS
 * ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 * "ENABLED IF"  → conditional field/section (frontend hides; backend validates)
 * "DERIVED"     → engine-computed; never asked of user
 * "PRE-FILLED"  → carried from Layer 0; user is not re-asked
 * "PROGRESSIVE" → collected after onboarding, before final ITR computation
 * Amounts       → INR whole units unless paired *_currency field says otherwise
 * Dates         → "YYYY-MM-DD"
 * Ratios        → decimal (0.10 = 10%)
 */
{

  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 1 — PROFILE
  // Screen 2A | Asked of all India users
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "profile": {

    "date_of_birth": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: REQUIRED
    // "YYYY-MM-DD"
    // Determines: senior citizen (60+) higher basic exemption under old regime,
    // super senior (80+) advance tax exemption, slab breakpoints.

    "pan": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // string (10 chars, AAAAA9999A format)
    // Permanent Account Number. Required for all India tax filings.

    "pan_aadhaar_linked": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLE IF pan
    // Is your PAN linked to Aadhaar?
    // CRITICAL: an unlinked PAN is INOPERATIVE — TDS doubles to 20% on most
    // streams under s.206AA, refunds are blocked, and ITR filing may be rejected.
    // Engine fires PAN_INOPERATIVE_ALERT if false and applies the doubled-TDS
    // assumption to all credit reconciliation.
    // NRIs: exempt from Aadhaar requirement; engine treats null as "exempt" if
    // residency lock = "NR".

    "tax_regime": null
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // "NEW" | "OLD" | null
    // DEFAULT for NRIs: "NEW". OLD is not legally blocked for NRIs.
    // RNOR / ROR → if null, engine auto-computes BOTH regimes and surfaces
    //              the lower liability. Requires `deductions` block to be filled.
    // NR         → defaults to "NEW" if null. Engine recomputes both on override.
    // Validation: business/professional income with prior s.115BAC(6) opt-out
    // is the only hard block (handled by DOM-03 inputs in `business_income`).
  },


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 2 — RESIDENCY DETAIL  +  THE LOCK
  // Screen 2A continued | Asked of all India users
  // Runs the RS-001 engine and writes the LOCK.
  //
  // SOURCE OF TRUTH: "India Residency (Tax Engine Logic).docx"
  // All input fields, ENABLED IF gates, and the lock derivation cascade
  // below are a direct translation of that document's boolean matrix.
  //
  // FIELD EVALUATION ORDER (frontend must respect this sequence):
  //   1. days_in_india_current_year (pre-filled from Layer 0)
  //   2. days_in_india_preceding_4_years_gte_365 (if days 60–181)
  //   3. employment_or_crew_status (if days 60–181 + preceding_4yr + Indian citizen)
  //   4. is_departure_year, ship_nationality (if employment/crew active)
  //   5. came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen (if employment = none)
  //   6. nr_years_last_10_gte_9 (if days >=182 OR came_on_visit = false)
  //   7. days_in_india_last_7_years_lte_729 (same gate as above)
  //   8. india_source_income_above_15l (if Layer 0 has_india_source_income = true)
  //   9. liable_to_tax_in_another_country_being_indian_citizen (DERIVED)
  //  10. final_india_residency_status (THE LOCK — DERIVED)
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "residency_detail": {

    // ── 1. Core day count (pre-filled from Layer 0) ───────────────────
    "days_in_india_current_year": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: REQUIRED
    // integer (0–366)
    // PRE-FILLED from Layer 0 india_days.
    // Exact total days physically present in India this FY (1 Apr 2025 – 31 Mar 2026).
    // Both arrival day and departure day count.
    // Overridden by trip_log computation once log is populated.

    // ── 2. Preceding 4-year day total ─────────────────────────────────
    "days_in_india_preceding_4_years_gte_365": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: days_in_india_current_year >= 60 AND days_in_india_current_year < 182
    //
    // Across the 4 preceding FYs combined (FY 2021-22 through FY 2024-25),
    // were you in India for 365 days or more in total?
    //
    // This is the Branch 2 prerequisite. If false AND days < 182, the 60-day
    // path does NOT trigger residency — the person falls through to the
    // Deemed Resident check or NR.

    // ── 3. Employment / crew detail ───────────────────────────────────
    "employment_or_crew_status": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // "employed_abroad" | "indian_ship_crew" | "foreign_ship_crew" | "none"
    //
    // ENABLED IF: ALL of the following are true:
    //   Layer 0 left_india_for_employment_this_year = true
    //   AND days_in_india_current_year >= 60
    //   AND days_in_india_current_year < 182
    //   AND days_in_india_preceding_4_years_gte_365 = true
    //   AND Layer 0 is_indian_citizen = true
    //
    // Gate rationale: the employment-departure exception (s.6(1) Explanation 1)
    // only applies to Indian citizens in the 60–181 day band who meet the
    // preceding-4-year test. If ANY gate condition fails, this field is hidden
    // and treated as "none" for lock derivation.
    //
    // Foreign ship crew: NOT covered by the employment exception (only Indian
    // ship crew under s.6(1)(c)).

    // ── 4. Departure year + ship nationality ──────────────────────────
    "is_departure_year": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: employment_or_crew_status NOT IN ["none", null]
    // First FY this person left India for this employment/crew role?
    // Per Binny Bansal [2026]: exception applies only in the departure year.
    // Engine auto-resets this flag every 1 April.

    "ship_nationality": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // "indian" | "foreign"
    // ENABLED IF: employment_or_crew_status IN ["indian_ship_crew", "foreign_ship_crew"]

    // ── 5. Visitor flag (NEW in v4.0) ─────────────────────────────────
    "came_on_visit_to_india_pio_citizen": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: employment_or_crew_status = "none"
    //             (i.e., the person is in the 60–181 + preceding_4yr >= 365
    //              path but is NOT leaving for employment)
    //
    // NOTE: if employment_or_crew_status was never shown (because the
    // employment gate conditions failed), this field is also NOT shown.
    // It is only relevant in the sub-tree where the person is in the
    // 60–181 band, has >= 365 preceding days, and is NOT an employee/crew.
    //
    // "Did you come to India on a visit, being a PIO or an Indian citizen?"
    //
    // If true → the person is on the Condition C (120-day visitor) path.
    //   Engine checks days >= 120 for s.6(6)(c) RNOR.
    // If false → the person is on the standard 60-day path.
    //   Engine checks Condition A (NR 9/10) and Condition B (< 729 days)
    //   for RNOR vs ROR.

    // ── 6. Historical travel — RNOR Condition A ───────────────────────
    "nr_years_last_10_gte_9": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: days_in_india_current_year >= 182
    //             OR came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen = false
    //
    // Of the last 10 FYs (FY 2015-16 through FY 2024-25), were you NR for
    // 9 or more of those years?
    // RNOR years count as NR for this test (RS-001 CA sign-off Item 1).
    // Condition A gate for RNOR under s.6(6)(a).
    //
    // Gate rationale: this question is asked in exactly two scenarios:
    //   (a) days >= 182 → person is RESIDENT via Branch 1; need Condition A/B
    //       to determine RNOR vs ROR.
    //   (b) came_on_visit = false → person is RESIDENT via the standard 60-day
    //       path (not a visitor); need Condition A/B to determine RNOR vs ROR.
    // In all other paths (visitor, deemed resident, NR), this field is not needed.

    // ── 7. Historical travel — RNOR Condition B ───────────────────────
    "days_in_india_last_7_years_lte_729": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: days_in_india_current_year >= 182
    //             OR came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen = false
    //
    // Across the 7 preceding FYs combined, were you in India for 729 days or fewer?
    // Threshold is "<= 729" inclusive per statutory "or less" language
    // (RS-001 CA sign-off Item 15).
    // Condition B gate for RNOR under s.6(6)(a).
    //
    // Same gate rationale as nr_years_last_10_gte_9.

    // ── 8. India-source income ₹15L gate (s.6(1A) Deemed Resident) ───
    "india_source_income_above_15l": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: Layer 0 has_india_source_income_or_assets = true
    //
    // Is your India-source income (excluding foreign earnings) above ₹15 lakh
    // this tax year?
    //
    // This is the s.6(1A) Deemed Resident threshold. If true AND the person is
    // an Indian citizen AND NOT liable to tax in another country → the person
    // becomes a Deemed Resident (always RNOR per s.6(6)(d)).
    //
    // NOTE: replaces the old `india_source_income_exact_inr` field. A boolean
    // is sufficient to set the residency lock; exact income computation happens
    // later in the income sections.

    // ── 9. Trip log (audit trail) ─────────────────────────────────────
    "current_year_trip_log": [],
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // Array of trip objects: [{ "arrival_date": "YYYY-MM-DD", "departure_date": "YYYY-MM-DD" }]
    // Days per trip = (departure_date − arrival_date + 1). Both days count.
    // When populated, overrides days_in_india_current_year for authoritative count.

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // DERIVED FIELDS (engine-computed, never asked of user)
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    "liable_to_tax_in_another_country_being_indian_citizen": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: DERIVED
    // DERIVED | bool
    //
    // Composite boolean derived from two Layer 0 pre-fills:
    //   Layer 0 is_indian_citizen = true AND Layer 0 liable_to_tax_in_another_country = true
    //     → TRUE
    //   ALL other combinations → FALSE
    //     (citizen=false, liable=true → FALSE)
    //     (citizen=true,  liable=false → FALSE)
    //     (citizen=false, liable=false → FALSE)
    //
    // This is the s.6(1A) Deemed Resident BLOCKER. When TRUE, the person
    // is an Indian citizen who IS liable to tax elsewhere — the Deemed
    // Resident provision is blocked, and the person remains NR (if they
    // don't qualify via the 182-day or 60-day paths).
    //
    // When FALSE, the Deemed Resident path is OPEN (subject to income > ₹15L).
    //
    // TRUTH TABLE (from source document):
    // ┌───────────────────┬──────────────────────────┬──────────┐
    // │ is_indian_citizen  │ liable_to_tax_elsewhere  │ Result   │
    // ├───────────────────┼──────────────────────────┼──────────┤
    // │ true               │ true                     │ TRUE     │
    // │ false              │ true                     │ FALSE    │
    // │ true               │ false                    │ FALSE    │
    // │ false              │ false                    │ FALSE    │
    // └───────────────────┴──────────────────────────┴──────────┘

    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // THE LOCK
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

    "final_india_residency_status": null
    // CLASSIFICATION: DERIVED
    // DERIVED | "NR" | "RNOR" | "ROR"
    // The LOCK. Computed by the RS-001 engine immediately after the questions
    // above are answered. NEVER asked of the user.
    //
    // ALL DOWNSTREAM SECTION GATES READ THIS FIELD. The lock must be set
    // before the frontend reveals any further screens.
    //
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    // EXHAUSTIVE DERIVATION CASCADE
    // Source: "India Residency (Tax Engine Logic).docx" — direct translation
    //
    // Abbreviations used below:
    //   DAYS     = days_in_india_current_year
    //   P4Y_365  = days_in_india_preceding_4_years_gte_365
    //   EMP      = employment_or_crew_status
    //   VISIT    = came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen
    //   NR9      = nr_years_last_10_gte_9
    //   D7_729   = days_in_india_last_7_years_lte_729
    //   INC_15L  = india_source_income_above_15l
    //   LTAC     = liable_to_tax_in_another_country_being_indian_citizen
    // ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    //
    // ─── ROR (2 paths) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
    //
    //   ROR-1: DAYS >= 182
    //          AND NR9 = false
    //          AND D7_729 = false
    //
    //   ROR-2: DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = false
    //          AND NR9 = false
    //          AND D7_729 = false
    //
    // ─── RNOR (9 paths) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
    //
    //   RNOR-1 (Condition A via 182-day):
    //          DAYS >= 182
    //          AND NR9 = true
    //
    //   RNOR-2 (Condition B via 182-day):
    //          DAYS >= 182
    //          AND D7_729 = true
    //
    //   RNOR-3 (Employment departure + Deemed Resident):
    //          DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = any value (not "none")
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = false
    //
    //   RNOR-4 (Visitor 120-day — Condition C):
    //          DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = true
    //          AND DAYS >= 120 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //
    //   RNOR-5 (Non-visitor, Condition A via 60-day):
    //          DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = false
    //          AND NR9 = true
    //
    //   RNOR-6 (Non-visitor, Condition B via 60-day):
    //          DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = false
    //          AND D7_729 = true
    //
    //   RNOR-7 (Deemed Resident — days < 60):
    //          DAYS < 60
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = false
    //
    //   RNOR-8 (Deemed Resident — 60–181, preceding 4yr < 365):
    //          DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = false
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = false
    //
    //   RNOR-9 (Visitor < 120 days + Deemed Resident):
    //          DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = true
    //          AND DAYS < 120
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = false
    //
    // ─── NR (8 paths) ────────────────────────────────────────────────
    //
    //   NR-1:  DAYS < 60
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = true
    //          (Deemed Resident blocked: Indian citizen liable elsewhere)
    //
    //   NR-2:  DAYS < 60
    //          AND INC_15L = false
    //          (No income threshold met; no path to residency)
    //
    //   NR-3:  DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = false
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = true
    //          (60-day path fails, Deemed Resident blocked)
    //
    //   NR-4:  DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = false
    //          AND INC_15L = false
    //          (60-day path fails, no Deemed Resident)
    //
    //   NR-5:  DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = true
    //          AND DAYS >= 120 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND INC_15L = false
    //          (Visitor 120-day path: meets days but income <= 15L)
    //
    //   NR-6:  DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = "none"
    //          AND VISIT = true
    //          AND DAYS < 120
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = true
    //          (Visitor < 120 days, Deemed Resident blocked)
    //
    //   NR-7:  DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = any value (not "none")
    //          AND INC_15L = false
    //          (Employment departure, income <= 15L → no Deemed Resident)
    //
    //   NR-8:  DAYS >= 60 AND DAYS < 182
    //          AND P4Y_365 = true
    //          AND EMP = any value (not "none")
    //          AND INC_15L = true
    //          AND LTAC = true
    //          (Employment departure, income > 15L but Deemed Resident blocked)
    //
    // ─── ENGINE IMPLEMENTATION NOTES ─────────────────────────────────
    //
    // 1. Evaluate top-down: DAYS >= 182 first, then DAYS 60–181 sub-tree,
    //    then DAYS < 60 sub-tree.
    //
    // 2. Within the 60–181 sub-tree, the FIRST fork is P4Y_365.
    //    If P4Y_365 = false → skip directly to Deemed Resident check
    //    (RNOR-8 if INC_15L + !LTAC, else NR-3 or NR-4).
    //
    // 3. If P4Y_365 = true → fork on EMP:
    //    EMP != "none" → employment path (RNOR-3 or NR-7/NR-8)
    //    EMP = "none"  → fork on VISIT:
    //      VISIT = true  → visitor path (RNOR-4, RNOR-9, NR-5, NR-6)
    //      VISIT = false → standard path (ROR-2, RNOR-5, RNOR-6)
    //
    // 4. Deemed Resident paths (RNOR-3, RNOR-7, RNOR-8, RNOR-9) are
    //    ALWAYS RNOR (never ROR) per s.6(6)(d). The Condition A/B check
    //    is NOT applied to Deemed Residents.
    //
    // 5. RNOR-1 and RNOR-2 are NOT mutually exclusive. A person with
    //    days >= 182 AND NR9 = true AND D7_729 = true matches BOTH.
    //    The result is the same (RNOR), so no conflict.
    //
    // 6. The employment_or_crew_status field may be null/hidden when the
    //    gate conditions don't fire. In that case, treat as "none" for
    //    lock derivation. Same for came_on_visit_to_india_pio_oci_citizen.
  },


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 3 — DTAA INPUT
  // Screen 2B | ENABLED IF: residency_detail.liable_to_tax_in_another_country_being_indian_citizen = true
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "dtaa": {

    "tax_residency_country": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 e.g. "US" | "AE" | "GB" | "SG" | "CA" | "IN"
    // Country where you currently pay personal income tax (your tax home).
    // Drives the entire treaty rate table.

    "is_us_resident_for_dtaa": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // ENABLED IF: tax_residency_country = "US"
    // Triggers the Savings Clause alert (DTAA Art.1(3)) — Form 67 required to
    // claim FTC for US taxes paid. Alert-only; does not block treaty benefit.
    // NOTE: detailed US residency classification lives in layer1_us.

    "trc_status": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // Do you have a valid Tax Residency Certificate (TRC) from your country of residence?
    // Without TRC → domestic rates apply (e.g. 30% NRO interest vs 10–15% treaty rate).

    "has_permanent_establishment_in_india": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    // bool
    // Do you have a fixed place of business, office, or dependent agent in India?
    // If true → DUAL_RESIDENCY_REVIEW flag fires; PE income taxable in India regardless of DTAA.

    "treaty_elections": [
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
      // Array — per-income-stream treaty rate election.
      // Engine picks lower of (domestic, treaty) per stream rather than per taxpayer.
      // ENABLE income_type BELOW QUESTIONS
      {
        "income_type": null,        
        // ENUM: "interest" | "dividend" | "royalty" | "fts" | "capital_gains"
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        "elected_rate": null,       // decimal e.g. 0.15
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        // FETCH FROM CONFIG
        "treaty_article": null      // string e.g. "Art. 11(2)(a) India-US DTAA"
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        // FETCH FROM CONFIG
      }
    ],

    "mfn_clause_invoked": null
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // bool
    // For treaties with MFN protocols (Netherlands, France, Switzerland, etc.).
    // Triggers per-stream rate recomputation against the lowest-rate comparable treaty.
  },


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 4 — PROGRESSIVE COMPLIANCE DOCUMENTS
  // PROGRESSIVE | Required before final ITR computation
  // ENABLED IF: dtaa.tax_residency_country is set
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "compliance_docs": {

    // ── TRC Details ── ENABLED IF: dtaa.trc_status = true
    "trc": {
      "validity_start_date": null,
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      // "YYYY-MM-DD"
      // Engine validates against each income payment date per Rule 21AB.

      "validity_end_date": null,
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      // "YYYY-MM-DD"

      "document_uploaded": null
      // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
      // bool — true = VERIFIED (treaty rates unlocked for ITR XML);
      //        false = DECLARED (provisional treaty rates with badge).
    },

    // ── Form 10F ── ENABLED IF: TRC is present but missing required fields
    "form_10f": {
      "is_filed": null,
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      // bool
      "ack_number": null
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      // string (15-digit ack from IT e-filing portal)
      // Electronic Form 10F mandatory for PAN holders. Treaty rates BLOCKED until ack entered.
    },

    // ── Section 197 Lower TDS Certificate ── PROGRESSIVE
    // ENABLED IF: dtaa section active (residency lock = "NR")
    // Decoupled from property gate — also covers NRO interest, dividends, etc.
    "section_197_cert": {
      "is_available": null,             // bool
      // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
      "rate": null,                     // decimal e.g. 0.05. ENABLED IF is_available = true
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
                                        // Overrides BOTH domestic AND DTAA rate.
      "validity_start_date": null,      // ENABLED IF is_available = true
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      "validity_end_date": null,        // ENABLED IF is_available = true
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      "covered_income_types": null      // array e.g. ["PROPERTY_CG","NRO_INTEREST","DIVIDEND"]
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
    },

    // ── Chapter XII-A Legacy Regime ── ENABLED IF nr_years_last_10_gte_9 = true OR lock = "NR"
    // Loosened gate (was NR-only in v2): a current ROR who was NR in prior years
    // may have previously elected XII-A and is bound by the s.115I one-way door.
    "chapter_xiia_elected": null
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // bool | PROGRESSIVE
    // Have you ever elected the Chapter XII-A special tax regime in any prior ITR?
    // Once opted out, CANNOT re-enter (s.115I) — flag for CA before any change.
  },


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 5 — BANK ACCOUNTS
  // ENABLED IF: residency lock IN ["NR","RNOR","ROR"]
  // Array — one object per account
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "bank_accounts": [
    {
      "bank_name": null,                  // string
      // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
      "account_type": null,               // "NRE"|"NRO"|"FCNR"|"RFC"|"GIFT_IFSC"|"SAVINGS"|"CURRENT"
      // CLASSIFICATION: REQUIRED
      "current_balance": null,            // number
      // CLASSIFICATION: REQUIRED
      "current_balance_currency": null,   // ISO 4217
      // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
      "annual_interest_rate": null,       // decimal e.g. 0.065
      // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
      "interest_credited_this_fy_inr": null,
      // CLASSIFICATION: REQUIRED
      // integer (INR) — actual interest credited this FY. Required for s.80TTA/TTB
      // computation and for distinguishing NRE-exempt from NRO-taxable interest.

      "account_conversion_date": null,
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      // "YYYY-MM-DD" | OPTIONAL
      // ENABLED IF: account_type = "NRE" AND lock changed to RNOR or ROR this FY.
      // CRITICAL: even 1 day as ROR = full year NRE interest taxable (no mid-year split).

      "fcnr_maturity_date": null,
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      // ENABLED IF: account_type = "FCNR"

      "nro_balance": null,                // ENABLED IF account_type = "NRO". Tracks USD 1M limit.
      // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      "nro_balance_currency": "INR"
      // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    }
  ],


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 6 — NRO REPATRIATION
  // ENABLED IF: any bank_account has account_type = "NRO"
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "nro_repatriation": {

    "cumulative_repatriated_usd_this_fy": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // number (USD). Annual limit: USD 1M aggregate. Alerts at 80% / 95%.

    "pending_repatriation_inr": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // number (INR). Determines Form 15CA/15CB trigger (INR 5L threshold).

    "tds_deducted_on_nro_balance": null
    // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
    // bool. false → TAX_CLEARANCE_REQUIRED fires.
  },


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 7 — IMMOVABLE PROPERTY
  // GATE: has_indian_property_transaction (asked first)
  // Applies to ALL residency statuses (rates and TDS obligations differ).
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "property": {

    "has_indian_property_transaction": null,
    // CLASSIFICATION: REQUIRED
    // bool — GATE
    // Selling, or have sold, Indian immovable property this FY?

    "properties": [
      {
        "property_type": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        // "residential"|"commercial"|"land"|"agricultural_rural"|"under_construction"
        // agricultural_rural → exempt (s.10(37)). Only "residential" qualifies for s.54.

        "acquisition_date": null,         // "YYYY-MM-DD". Inherited: original owner's date.
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "actual_cost": null,              // number (INR)
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "actual_cost_currency": null,     // ISO 4217
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        "pre_2001_fmv_inr": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        // ENABLED IF: acquisition_date < "2001-04-01"
        // Engine uses MAX(actual_cost, pre_2001_fmv_inr) as cost basis.

        "transfer_expenses_inr": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        // number (INR). Brokerage, legal fees, stamp duty paid by seller.
        // Statutorily deductible from sale consideration before CG computation.

        "sale_date": null,                // "YYYY-MM-DD"
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
                                          // FA 2024: pre-23 Jul → 20% indexed (residents only);
                                          //          post-23 Jul → 12.5% no indexation;
                                          //          NRIs: always 12.5% post Jul 2024.
        "sale_consideration": null,       // number (INR)
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "sale_consideration_currency": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL

        "stamp_duty_value": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        // number (INR) — circle rate at SALE date.
        // s.50C: if SDV > sale price by > 10%, SDV used as deemed consideration.
        "stamp_duty_value_currency": "INR",
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL

        // ── Buyer-side TDS (NRI sales — s.195) ──
        "buyer_tan": null,                // string. ENABLED IF lock = "NR"
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "buyer_tds_deducted_inr": null,   // integer. ENABLED IF lock = "NR"
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "buyer_tds_challan_number": null, // string.  ENABLED IF lock = "NR"
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        // s.195 TDS = 12.5% + surcharge + cess on FULL sale value (not gain) for NRI sellers
        // unless Section 197 cert exists. Required for 26AS reconciliation.

        "is_joint_property": null,        // bool
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        "ownership_percentage": null,     // 1–100. ENABLED IF is_joint_property = true
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL

        "is_inherited": null,             // bool
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        "original_owner_acquisition_date": null,  // ENABLED IF is_inherited = true
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "original_owner_cost": null,              // ENABLED IF is_inherited = true
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "original_owner_cost_currency": null,     // ENABLED IF is_inherited = true
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL

        // ── Reinvestment Exemptions (LTCG only) ──
        "reinvestment_exemption_claimed": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        // "none" | "s54" | "s54f" | "s54ec"

        "new_property_cost": null,           // ENABLED IF claimed IN ["s54","s54f"]. Cap ₹10Cr.
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "new_property_cost_currency": "INR",
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        "new_property_purchase_date": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL

        "s54_two_house_option": null,
        // CLASSIFICATION: DERIVED
        // DERIVED | bool
        // TRUE when claimed = "s54" AND LTCG <= ₹2 Cr AND not previously exercised.

        "bond_investment": null,             // ENABLED IF claimed = "s54ec". Cap ₹50L.
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
        "bond_investment_currency": "INR",
        // CLASSIFICATION: OPTIONAL
        "bond_investment_date": null         // Within 6 months of sale_date. 5-year lock.
        // CLASSIFICATION: CONDITIONAL
      }
    ]
  },


  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  // SECTION 8 — FINANCIAL HOLDINGS (listed equity, MFs, ETFs, bonds)
  // Applies to ALL residency statuses
  // ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  "financial_holdings": {

